Preheat oven: 350 degrees Carefully cut off a thin slice from the top of each tomato. Hollow out pulp, leaving thin layer inside, discard extra pulp. Turn tomatoes upside down on paper towel to drain. In a bowl, combine all remainingingredients. Mix well. Spoon mixture into tomatoes. Spray cookie sheet with non-stick vegetable spray. Place tomatoes on cookie sheet. Bake approximately 15 minutes, or until cheese is melty.